	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I never messed with the original Zapper as well, only fixed tons of clones for Famiclones, they had broken cords/plugs for the most part. In those, there was no resonator, just a sensor, transistor, and a couple resistors. In the past I have heard many times that people were able to fake hit detection by pointing the sensor on a light bulb.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
