	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Should be easy to test on hardware, provided you've got a zapper and some dev cart (e.g. PowerPak).<br /><br />The test I imagine is: each, say, 30 vblanks, toogle the display from all black to all white and vice-versa. Continuously poll the &quot;detection&quot; bit, as soon as it is  set, output a loud beep, otherwise silence. The slowly flashing screen is to verify that the &quot;beeper&quot; code works reliably when the zapper points the TV, then after we can see if it beeps when the zapper points a bright light source.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


